CSC457 has the course title "Computer Networks". CSC457 is a 4.0 credit course taught by Adam Purtee. CSC457 is offered every "Summer Spring Fall ". Introduction to computer networks and computer communication: Architecture and Protocols:. Design of protocols for error recovery, reliable delivery, routing and congestion control. Store-and-forward networks, satellite networks, local area networks and locally distributed systems. Case studies of networks, protocols and protocol families. Emphasis on software design issues in computer communication.